    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:comment>Workholding devices (vises, chucks, fixtures, pallet systems) are multi-part assemblies with role-bearing components (jaws, screws, locating pins, clamping bodies), so they retain gufo:FunctionalComplex membership directly. The pc:ProcessAuxiliary parent only contributes the gufo:Object placement.</rdfs:comment>
