  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/meta#SentinelCodeElement">
    <rdfs:label>Sentinel Code Element</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/CodesAndCodeSets/CodeElement"/>
    <rdfs:comment>A CodeElement that does not designate a canonical concept in the taxonomy. Two flavors: (1) absence-of-answer sentinels ("No Response", "Refused", "Don't Know") record that the respondent opted out; (2) free-text fallbacks ("Other (Please specify)") record that the respondent picked something outside the canonical concept space and supplied a string (additionally signalled by amtmeta:promptsFreeText "true"). The string itself is form / storage runtime data and is NOT stored in the ontology. Both flavors are exempt from the cmns-dsg:designates &gt;=1 constraint (codeset-shapes.ttl) and forbidden from carrying any cmns-dsg:designates targets -- a code that points at a canonical concept contradicts the purpose of either flavor.</rdfs:comment>
  </rdf:Description>
